<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a120a08-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577"><num value="6577">§ 6577.</num><heading> Involvement by other agencies and organizations</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out this subchapter, the Secretary of Agriculture may consult with—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a09-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> nonindustrial private forest landowners;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a0a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> other Federal agencies;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a0b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> State fish and wildlife agencies;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a0c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> State forestry agencies;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a0d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> State environmental quality agencies;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a0e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/6"><num value="6">(6)</num><content> other State conservation agencies; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a120a0f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s6577/7"><num value="7">(7)</num><content> nonprofit conservation organizations.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a120a10-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/148/tV/s507">Pub. L. 108–148, title V, § 507</ref>, <date date="2003-12-03">Dec. 3, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/1914">117 Stat. 1914</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
